@divided_government_result
on-arrival: {!
if (!Q.selected_senate_coalition && !Q.non_dem_senate_control) {
    Q.selected_senate_coalition = "Democratic-led Senate coalition";
    Q.governing_senate_support = Q.best_dem_senate || Q.governing_senate_support || 0;
}
var cabinetParty = Q.president_party || "SPD";
Q.foreign_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.interior_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.justice_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.labor_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.reichswehr_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.economic_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.finance_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.agriculture_minister_party = cabinetParty;
!}

Congress is divided against the administration.

House: [+ selected_house_coalition +]

Senate: [+ selected_senate_coalition +]

[? if non_dem_house_control = 1 and non_dem_senate_control = 1 : Opposition forces control both chambers. The president keeps the executive branch, but legislation will require hostile bargaining or later elections. ?]
[? if non_dem_house_control = 1 and non_dem_senate_control = 0 : The administration has a Senate path, but the House is controlled by the opposition. ?]
[? if non_dem_house_control = 0 and non_dem_senate_control = 1 : The administration has a House organizing coalition, but the Senate is controlled by the opposition. ?]

- @root: Continue.

# TODO: black-brown coalition


@popular_front_coalition
title: A popular-front Senate coalition?
subtitle: Democratic Party + Socialist Party of America + Farmer-Labor [? if sapd_formed: + left splinters ?]([+ popular_senate +]%)
unavailable-subtitle: Democratic Party + Socialist Party of America + Farmer-Labor [? if sapd_formed: + left splinters ?]([+ popular_senate +]%) - [? if ((kpd_relation < 65 and kpd_party_leader == "Thälmann") or (kpd_relation < 45 and kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators")): We do not have good enough relations with the Socialist Party of America. ?][? if (z_relation < 45 and z_party_leader == "Joos") or (z_relation < 65 and z_party_leader != "Joos" and kpd_party_leader != "Conciliators") or (z_relation < 55 and z_party_leader != "Joos" and kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators"): We do not have good enough relations with Farmer-Labor. ?][? if communist_coalition < 3 : The socialists are unwilling to compromise enough for coalition government. ?]
view-if: popular_senate >= 50
choose-if: (((kpd_relation >= 65 and kpd_party_leader == "Thälmann") or (kpd_relation >= 45 and kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators")) and ((z_relation >= 45 and z_party_leader == "Joos") or (z_relation >= 65 and z_party_leader != "Joos" and kpd_party_leader != "Conciliators") or (z_relation >= 55 and z_party_leader != "Joos" and kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators")) and communist_coalition >= 3) or (z_party_leader == "Joos" and kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators" and z_relation >= 30 and kpd_relation >= 30)

Could we really form a coalition that included Farmer-Labor and the Socialist Party of America? It seems fragile, but if both sides are willing to bargain, it is not impossible. The Liberty League is not part of this coalition; they are organizing against the New Deal from the right.

The far-right might attempt a coup, if such a coalition were formed.

- @popular_front_2: Form the Popular Front!
- @great_popular_front: Form the Popular Front!

@popular_front_2
view-if: z_party_leader != "Joos" or kpd_party_leader != "Conciliators"

Somehow, both the Communists and Center are at the very least willing to entertain negotiations. Of course, SPA radicals and Center conservatives derail the negotiations almost immediately. The SPA demands leadership of the coalition for themselves and their chairman Ernst Thälmann, [? if spd_r > kpd_r : despite our higher vote share, ?]while the Center is offended by the prospect of helping Bolsheviks enter government. *Something* must be done to restore balance.

- @popular_front_resources
- @popular_front_democracy
- @popular_front_braun
- @coalition_menu: This is impossible. Try another governing arrangement.

@popular_front_resources
title: Use our resources to smooth things over.
unavailable-subtitle: Required: 4 resources
subtitle: -4 resources
choose-if: resources >= 4
on-arrival: resources -= 4
go-to: popular_front_success

@popular_front_democracy
title: Convince the SPA to accept coalition discipline.
subtitle: [? if kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators" : The conciliator leadership of the SPA at least claims to support a popular front. ?]
unavailable-subtitle: Our relationship with the SPA is not high enough.
choose-if: (kpd_relation >= 60 and communist_coalition >= 3) or kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators"
go-to: popular_front_success

@popular_front_braun
title: Use pressure from President Braun to force the parties to cooperate.
view-if: president == "Braun"
go-to: popular_front_success

@great_popular_front
view-if: z_party_leader == "Joos" and kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators"
on-arrival: spd_in_government = 1; in_popular_front = 1; chancellor = "Breitscheid"; chancellor_party = "SPD"; kpd_relation += 10; coup_progress += 2; in_left_front = 0; in_weimar_coalition = 0; in_grand_coalition = 0; coalition_dissent = 0;
achievement: grosse_volksfront
go-to: popular_front_civil_war if coup_progress >= 10; popular_front_no_civil_war if coup_progress < 10

Somehow, the coalition is successfully formed! The conciliatory leadership of the Center Party and SPA helped make the negotiations possible. We still need a speaker; the only acceptable choice among the parties was Rudolf Breitscheid of the SPD, acceptable to the Center and SPA [? if president == "the old president" : as well as President the old president, albeit extremely reluctantly ?].

@popular_front_success
on-arrival: selected_senate_coalition = "Popular front coalition"; governing_senate_support = popular_senate; bill_coalition_viable = 1 if non_dem_house_control = 0; spd_in_government = 1; in_popular_front = 1; chancellor = "Breitscheid"; chancellor_party = "SPD"; kpd_relation += 10; coup_progress += 2; in_left_front = 0; in_weimar_coalition = 0; in_grand_coalition = 0; coalition_dissent = 0;
go-to: divided_government_result if non_dem_house_control = 1; popular_front_civil_war if non_dem_house_control = 0 and coup_progress >= 10; popular_front_no_civil_war if non_dem_house_control = 0 and coup_progress < 10
achievement: volksfront

Somehow, surprisingly, the coalition is successfully formed! We still need a speaker; the only acceptable choice among the parties was Rudolf Breitscheid of the SPD, acceptable to the Center and SPA [? if president == "the old president" : as well as President the old president, albeit extremely reluctantly ?].

@popular_front_no_civil_war
on-arrival: kpd_goals_seen = 0; finance_minister_party = "Z"; interior_minister_party = "Z"; economic_minister_party = "Z"; labor_minister_party = "Z"; foreign_minister_party = "Z"; agriculture_minister_party = "Z"; reichswehr_minister = "I"; leverage = spd_r + kpd_r;
achievement: volksfront

In response to the SPA's entrance into the government, the right-wing takes a "wait-and-see" approach for now. They expect that the Popular Front government will be unstable and incompetent, and will collapse of its own accord, discrediting the left and center and eventually enabling the destruction of the Weimar Republic. Our task is to prove them wrong.

The SPA has taken an abstentionist position with regards to ministries. They claim to be participating as the "loyal opposition" within the Popular Front government, supporting us from the outside while also running their own propaganda campaigns to turn workers to their side. They seem to expect that the Popular Front would inevitably fail, and that our failure would benefit them.

- @ministries: First, we must select our ministries.


@popular_front_civil_war
on-arrival: kpd_relation = 80; reichswehr_loyalty += 0.25;

In response to the SPA's entrance into the government, the right-wing immediately launches a coup attempt. Troops of the Liberty League auxiliaries and Silver Legion SA enter Berlin and immediately begin clashing with our supporters! Reactionary officers within the Defense Department have taken their troops out of the barracks and joined them with the Liberty League auxiliaries to stop us from taking power.

The Center manages to diffuse some of the hostility from the Defense Department and the Liberty League auxiliaries, but fail to prevent the outbreak of fighting. We are forced to fight on the same side as the SPA, whether we want to or not.

- @civil_war: A civil war, then.



@far_right_coalition
title: Far-right coalition
subtitle: National Union for Social Justice + Silver Legion ([+ far_right_senate +]%)
view-if: far_right_senate >= 50
go-to: far_right_win if (year >= 1932 or nsdap_r >= 44) and president != "Braun"; far_right_fail if (year < 1932 and nsdap_r < 44) and president != "Braun"; far_right_braun if president == "Braun"
priority: 2

There are enough votes for the Silver Legion and the DNVP to form a coalition. [+ nsdap_leader +] has made his participation in government contingent on being appointed speaker. It is up to President [+ president +] to decide.

@far_right_win
on-arrival: chancellor = nsdap_leader; chancellor_party = "NSDAP"

[? if president == "the old president" : President the old president's camarilla ?][? if president == "Braun" : President Braun somehow ?] has decided that [+ nsdap_leader +] must be speaker [? if president == "the old president": , and the aging president accepts their recommendations. ?][? if president == "Braun" : because it is what the constitution would stipulate. ?]

- @hitler_takes_power: What do we do now?


@far_right_fail
on-arrival: chancellor = "Schleicher"; chancellor_party = "I"; pro_republic -= 10; next_election_time = time+5; next_election_month = month + 5; next_election_year = year; next_election_year += 1 if next_election_month > 12; next_election_month -= 12 if next_election_month > 12;

The reactionary establishment is still very skeptical of the Silver Legion, so instead, [+ president +] appoints Kurt von the conservative operator, a former general, as speaker, to try to "tame" the Silver Legion.

the conservative operator's government is deeply unpopular among all parties of the Congress. Despite his support for a coalition with the Silver Legion, the Silver Legion want power all to themselves, without the conservative operator.

New elections have been set for [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +].

@far_right_braun
on-arrival: coup_progress += 2

President Braun faces a dilemma. Is it "democratic" to let democracy be destroyed, if the majority of voters have willed it so? Some, even on the left, suggest that the Silver Legion would not *truly* be as horrific as their platform suggests, and that giving them power would let them discredit themselves in the eyes of the public.

Alternatively, Braun could use the emergency powers of the presidency. Article 48 has been used by the old president to promulgate anti-democratic and anti-worker policies; can Article 48 be used for good as well as evil?

- @emergency_braun: We will form an emergency government with Braun's support.
- @new_elections: We will have new elections.
- @far_right_win: Let the Silver Legion form their government.


@left_coalition
title: Is a labor-left Senate coalition possible?
subtitle: Democratic Party + Socialist Party of America [? if sapd_formed: + left splinters ?] ([+ left_senate +]%)
unavailable-subtitle: Democratic Party + Socialist Party of America [? if sapd_formed: + left splinters ?] ([+ left_senate +]%). [? if kpd_relation < 50 : We do not have adequate relations with the Socialist Party of America. ?][? if communist_coalition < 3 : The socialists are too committed to their radical ways to partake in government. ?]
view-if: left_senate >= 50
choose-if: (kpd_relation >= 50 or (kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators" and kpd_relation >= 40)) and communist_coalition >= 3

There are enough votes for a SPD + SPA coalition government, if such a thing were actually possible.

The far-right might attempt a coup, if such a coalition were formed.

- @left_coalition_impossible: This is impossible.
- @left_coalition_possible: This could be possible.

@left_coalition_impossible
go-to: coalition_menu

A far left coalition is impossible.


@left_coalition_possible

The SPA is still very reluctant to join a coalition, despite grassroots friendliness between our memberships. The Stalinist leadership is vehemently against such a thing. They demand the appointment of Ernst Thälmann as speaker in exchange for a coalition. [? if president == "the old president" : There is no chance whatsoever that President the old president would approve of the appointment of a die-hard communist as speaker. ?] Alternatively, if our relations with them are good enough, we could convince them to support the appointment of one of our centrist or left-leaning members as speaker.

- @thalmann_speaker: Appoint Thälmann as speaker.
- @left_coalition_resources
- @left_coalition_relations
- @coalition_menu: Try a different governing arrangement.

@thalmann_speaker
choose-if: president == "Braun" and reformist_strength + neorevisionist_strength < left_strength
unavailable-subtitle: [? if president != "Braun": President [+ president +] would never allow such a thing. ?] [? if reformist_strength >= left_strength : Most in the parliamentary party would not support Thälmann as speaker. ?]
on-arrival: chancellor = "Thälmann"; chancellor_party = "KPD"; kpd_relation = 80; in_left_front = 1; spd_in_government = 1 

With great reluctance, President [+ president +] appoints [+ speaker +] as speaker.

Immediately, [+ speaker +] goes to work building a "Soviet the republic": consolidating as much power as possible in the SPA, purging state institutions of anti-communists, and sending street fighters against the "enemies of the people".

In response to [+ speaker +] being appointed Speaker, the right-wing forces launches almost immediately launch an attempted coup. Troops of the Liberty League auxiliaries and Silver Legion SA enter Berlin and immediately begin clashing with our supporters! Reactionary officers within the Defense Department have taken their troops out of the barracks and joined them with the Liberty League auxiliaries to stop the SPA from taking power. We are forced to be on the same side as the SPA, whether we want to or not.

- @civil_war


@left_coalition_resources
title: Use our resources to smooth things over.
unavailable-subtitle: Required: 3 resources
subtitle: -3 resources
choose-if: resources >= 3
on-arrival: resources -= 3
go-to: left_coalition_success

@left_coalition_relations
title: Convince the SPA to accept coalition discipline.
unavailable-subtitle: Our relationships with the SPA are not good enough.
choose-if: kpd_relation >= 60 or kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators"
go-to: left_coalition_success


@left_coalition_success
on-arrival: selected_senate_coalition = "Labor-left coalition"; governing_senate_support = left_senate; bill_coalition_viable = 1 if non_dem_house_control = 0; spd_in_government = 1; in_left_front = 1; chancellor = "Breitscheid"; chancellor_party = "SPD"; coup_progress += 3; capital_strike_progress += 2; in_popular_front = 0; in_grand_coalition = 0; in_weimar_coalition = 0; kpd_relation += 10
go-to: divided_government_result if non_dem_house_control = 1; left_coalition_civil_war if non_dem_house_control = 0 and coup_progress >= 10; left_coalition_no_civil_war if non_dem_house_control = 0 and coup_progress < 10
achievement: einheitsfront

Somehow, surprisingly, the left coalition is successfully formed, without appointing Thälmann as speaker. The consensus choice for speaker, accepted by the SPD, SPA, and President [+ president +], is Rudolf Breitscheid, who belongs to the centrist faction of the SPD, but was acceptable to the left due to his previous membership in the left-wing anti-war USPD.

# just raise the coup limit, don't immediately go to civil war

@left_coalition_no_civil_war
on-arrival: kpd_goals_seen = 0; foreign_minister_party = "SPD"; interior_minister_party = "SPD"; justice_minister_party = "SPD"; labor_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_minister_party = "SPD"; economic_minister_party = "SPD"; finance_minister_party = "SPD"; agriculture_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.05

In response to the SPA's entrance into the government, the right-wing takes a "wait-and-see" approach for now. They expect that our government will be unstable and incompetent, and will collapse of its own accord, discrediting the left and eventually enabling the destruction of the Weimar Republic. Our task is to prove them wrong.

The SPA has taken an abstentionist position with regards to ministries. They claim to be participating as the "loyal opposition" in the worker's government, supporting us from the outside while also running their own propaganda campaigns to turn workers to their side. They seem to expect that we would inevitably fail, and that our failure would benefit them. 

Whatever their reasoning is, the SPD has control over the ministries of government.

@left_coalition_civil_war
on-arrival: reichswehr_loyalty += 0.1

In response to the SPA's entrance into the government, the right-wing immediately launches a coup attempt. Troops of the Liberty League auxiliaries and Silver Legion SA enter Berlin and begin clashing with our supporters. Reactionary officers within the Defense Department have taken their troops out of the barracks and joined them with the Liberty League auxiliaries to stop us from taking power.

- @civil_war: A civil war, then.



@right_coalition
title: Refuse to form a government, so that a right-wing coalition may be formed.
subtitle: Farmer-Labor conservatives + Republican Party + Silver Legion-aligned minor parties ([+ right_senate +]%)
unavailable-subtitle: Reactionary conservatives are not interested in a stable coalition with Farmer-Labor.
view-if: right_senate >= 50
