Our experts have checked the constitution, and have discovered that there is no specific prohibition against the Speaker also being the President (the President may not be a member of the Congress; there is no law saying that the Speaker *must* be a member of the Congress).

Thus, we have Speaker-President Otto Braun. He claims that he will resign as soon as the economic-political crisis is over. The right-wing parties, who were once clamoring to replace parliamentary rule with dictatorship or monarchy, are now clamoring for the restoration of democracy.

