@grand_coalition_z_lead_2

The Farmer-Labor Speaker is likely to be Floyd B. Olson. He can hold agrarian and labor-populist votes, but he will expect real concessions on relief, farm debt, and committee influence. [? if austerity >= 2 : Because prior budget restraint damaged the coalition, many Democrats are reluctant to participate again. Some support outside toleration to keep extremists out of power; others prefer opposition and a sharper Democratic identity. ?]

Olson is not opposed to a coalition with us. Alternatively, we could enter a toleration agreement.

- @join_bruning: Join the Farmer-Labor-led coalition.
- @bruning_oppo: Join the opposition.
- @toleration_bruning: We will tolerate a minority Farmer-Labor government.
- @unity_government

@join_bruning
view-if: grand_senate >= 50 or neo_weimar_senate >= 50
on-arrival: spd_in_government = 1; spd_toleration = 0; in_grand_coalition = 1; chancellor = "Brüning"; chancellor_party = "Z"; foreign_minister_party = "DVP"; interior_minister_party = "Z"; justice_minister_party = "Z"; labor_minister_party = "Z"; reichswehr_minister_party = "I"; economic_minister_party = "Z"; finance_minister_party = "Z"; agriculture_minister_party = "Z"; leverage = 25 if leverage >= 25;
go-to: ministries

Floyd B. Olson welcomes us into the organizing coalition. Now, we have to settle the committee and department bargain.

@bruning_oppo
on-arrival: spd_in_government = 0; spd_toleration = 0; chancellor = "Brüning"; chancellor_party = "Z"; foreign_minister_party = "DVP"; interior_minister_party = "Z"; justice_minister_party = "Z"; labor_minister_party = "Z"; reichswehr_minister_party = "I"; economic_minister_party = "Z"; finance_minister_party = "Z"; agriculture_minister_party = "Z"; grand_coalition_failed = 1

By refusing to join or tolerate the stabilization coalition, we throw the balance of Congress to the right. [? if right_coalition >= 50 : There are enough votes for a conservative bloc with Republican, Liberty League, and NUSJ support, but NUSJ and the Silver Legion remain unreliable anti-system forces. ?][? if right_coalition < 50 : There are not enough votes for a coherent conservative majority, and NUSJ and the Silver Legion remain hostile to constitutional coalition government. ?]

If we do not at least tolerate the arrangement, there will be new elections in a few months. In the meantime, the President and Speaker will try to govern through executive action, committee leverage, and emergency appropriations. It is not clear we will do any better in the next election.

- @join_bruning: Join the Farmer-Labor-led coalition.
- @toleration_bruning: We will tolerate Olson after all.
- @brauns_dilemma
- @new_elections: New elections, it is!


@new_elections
on-arrival: {!
Q.next_election_month = Q.month + 3;
Q.next_election_time = Q.time + 3;
if (Q.next_election_month > 12) {
    Q.next_election_month -= 12;
    Q.next_election_year = Q.year + 1;
} else {
    Q.next_election_year = Q.year;
}
if (Q.chancellor == "Brüning") {
    Q.z_relation -= 5;
    Q.dvp_relation -= 5;
}
Q.pro_republic -= 8;
Q.workers_spd -= 5;
Q.new_middle_spd -= 5;
Q.old_middle_spd -= 5;
Q.rural_spd -= 5;
Q.catholics_spd -= 3;
Q.new_middle_dvp -= 8;
Q.old_middle_dvp -= 8;
Q.new_middle_ddp -= 5;
Q.old_middle_ddp -= 10;
Q.rural_dnvp -= 5;
Q.workers_nsdap += 5;
Q.old_middle_nsdap += 6;
Q.new_middle_nsdap += 6;
Q.rural_nsdap += 6;
Q.unemployed_nsdap += 5;
// Thresholds are kind of arbitrary - adjusted because of negative economic effects on pro_republic
if (Q.pro_republic < 45 && Q.pro_republic >= 36) {
    Q.workers_spd -= 6;
}
if (Q.pro_republic < 36) {
    // TODO: if you pursue a consistently revolutionary course, you might avoid this? But you might also cause a coalition between Hitler and the Center.
    Q.z_relation -= 5;
    Q.dvp_relation -= 5;
    Q.workers_spd *= 0.85;
    Q.unemployed_spd -= 2;
    Q.new_middle_spd -= 5;
    Q.old_middle_spd -= 5;
    Q.rural_spd -= 5;
    Q.catholics_spd -= 3;
    Q.workers_nsdap += 8;
    Q.old_middle_nsdap += 8;
    Q.new_middle_nsdap += 8;
    Q.rural_nsdap += 8;
    Q.unemployed_nsdap += 8;   
}
if (Q.far_right_coalition >= 50) {
    Q.sa_strength += 100;
    Q.sh_strength += 100;
    Q.coup_progress += 3;
}
!}

There is no path to a workable Congress majority or minority government. The next elections are set for [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +].

The people's faith in democracy is shaken by this ordeal. Of course, the Silver Legion are exploiting the instability to claim that democracy is unworkable, and that the republic needs a strong leader.


@toleration_bruning
choose-if: neo_weimar_coalition >= 50
unavailable-subtitle: The parties supporting the Farmer-Labor-led arrangement do not have a majority.
on-arrival: spd_in_government = 0; spd_toleration = 1; minority_government = 1; chancellor = "Brüning"; chancellor_party = "Z"; foreign_minister_party = "DVP"; interior_minister_party = "Z"; justice_minister_party = "I"; labor_minister_party = "Z"; reichswehr_minister_party = "I"; economic_minister_party = ddp_name; finance_minister_party = "DVP"; agriculture_minister_party = "Z"; pro_republic -= 4; new_middle_dvp -= 5; new_middle_ddp -= 5; old_middle_dvp -= 5; old_middle_ddp -= 5; old_middle_nsdap += 5; new_middle_nsdap += 5; rural_dnvp -= 5;

We have decided to tolerate Olson's organizing arrangement. We will vote against no-confidence moves and keep the far right out of power, but we will not directly own the congressional agenda.

@grand_coalition_fail
on-arrival: grand_coalition_failed = 1

Unfortunately, the Republican bloc is unwilling to enter another stabilization coalition with the Democrats, so the arrangement cannot be formed.

- @no_majority: Thus, there is no clear majority.
- @brauns_dilemma
- @right_coalition_2: Perhaps a right-wing coalition may form.
- @beg_dvp: Perhaps we could ask Republican moderates to change their minds?
- @unity_government
- @coalition_menu: What are the other governing arrangements?


@beg_dvp
view-if: dvp_relation >= 15
go-to: dvp_conservative if stresemann_dead == 1; dvp_majority if stresemann_dead == 0

@dvp_majority
go-to: join_bruning

Under the influence of Gustav Stresemann, the DVP agrees to allow us into the coalition, and so does the BVP.


@dvp_conservative

The DVP asks us to adhere to their conservative economic policies (that is, extreme austerity and labor discipline) in exchange for us joining the coalition.

- @beg_dvp_2: But they would not have a majority without the SPD! The DNVP and Silver Legion have no interest in participating in government.
- @no_majority: There is no chance that we would agree.
- @brauns_dilemma
- @coalition_menu: What are the other governing arrangements?


@beg_dvp_2
go-to: beg_dvp_succeed; beg_dvp_fail

We make the case that without the SPD, there is no parliamentary majority, given the DNVP and Silver Legion's hostility to constitutional government.

@beg_dvp_succeed
go-to: join_bruning

Somehow, we succeed in convincing them! We are now in a coalition.


@beg_dvp_fail
go-to: no_majority

As expected, the DVP is too set in their anti-democratic ways.



@grand_coalition_spd_lead
on-arrival: leverage -= 15 if dvp_relation < 20

As expected, the Democratic Party is the largest party, and this time, we are expected to take the lead role in organizing the House, including selecting the Speaker. President [+ president +] has asked us to assemble a working congressional majority.

[? if dvp_relation < 20 : As our relation with the DVP is poor, they are demanding more minister posts in order to remain part of the coalition. ?]

Who should be Speaker of the House?

