@presidential_cabinet
on-arrival: {!
var cabinetParty = Q.president_party || Q.chancellor_party || "SPD";
Q.foreign_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.interior_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.justice_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.labor_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.reichswehr_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.economic_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.finance_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.agriculture_minister_party = cabinetParty;
Q.bill_coalition_viable = Q.governing_senate_support >= 50 ? 1 : 0;
!}

Because the presidency controls the executive branch, cabinet departments stay with the president's party. The congressional coalition determines the Speaker, committee control, confirmations, and whether bills can pass; it does not hand cabinet departments to coalition partners.

- @root: Continue.

